Knowledge Manager Demo
Agent Profiles
14 Jun 2026

* Start the Knowledge Manager

Click Run to start the Knowledge Manager documentation server.

Open the running servers after they start:

- Documentation: [[http://localhost:18081][http://localhost:18081]]
- Control (lifecycle exit): [[http://127.0.0.1:18082][http://127.0.0.1:18082]]
- Monitor: [[http://localhost:18084/ui/][http://localhost:18084/ui/]]

.play start_knowledge_manager.go /START OMIT/,/END OMIT/

* Call the lifecycle exit API

After the Knowledge Manager is running, post the exit request to its control
server (default `http://127.0.0.1:18082/api/lifecycle/exit`, HTTP 202 Accepted).
The request is itself a declarative agent, not a bespoke HTTP client: a one-state
machine binds the rest tool, posts the fixed request, and reaches a terminal
`succeeded` state. Run it through the same interpreter that runs the curator:

	agent --profile demo/call-lifecycle-exit/profile.yaml --directory .

The REST authority lives in the profile, not in runtime input:

.code call-lifecycle-exit/rest.yaml /post_exit:/,/signal: ExitAccepted/
